cp|8|AT|

^B@2^*BHoward Schutzman: ^*N|cp||at|Although, these days, the majority play that bidding 2C over 1@D establishes a game force, I prefers to play that 2@C over 1@D only guarantees invitational values (10+ points). The reason is that there is no good bid available when responder holds an invitational hand with clubs. Over 1 of a major, responder has the option of bidding a forcing NT with invitational values. But there is no forcing NT available over 1@D.|
